From: Dom Cobley <popcornmix@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jan 2025 16:24:09 +0000
Subject: clk: bcm: rpi: Allow cpufreq driver to also adjust gpu clocks
Git-commit: c911a66059a23e284dcfd00cf847368c0a2fa6c8
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc1
References: git-fixes

For performance/power it is beneficial to adjust gpu clocks with arm clock.
This is how the downstream cpufreq driver works

Acked-by: Stephen Boyd <sboyd@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Dom Cobley <popcornmix@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Dave Stevenson <dave.stevenson@raspberrypi.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250116-bcm2712-clk-updates-v1-2-10bc92ffbf41@raspberrypi.com
Reviewed-by: Florian Fainelli <florian.fainelli@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Stephen Boyd <sboyd@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Ivan T. Ivanov <iivanov@suse.de>
---
 drivers/clk/bcm/clk-raspberrypi.c |    1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/clk/bcm/clk-raspberrypi.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/bcm/clk-raspberrypi.c
@@ -156,7 +156,6 @@ static int raspberrypi_clock_property(st
 	struct raspberrypi_firmware_prop msg = {
 		.id = cpu_to_le32(data->id),
 		.val = cpu_to_le32(*val),
-		.disable_turbo = cpu_to_le32(1),
 	};
 	int ret;
 
